Small Straws In A Soft Wind by Marsha Burns
Now is the time when you can find answers to questions or conclusions to
long-standing dilemmas.  You can now get closure on things that have
kept you from moving forward in the flow of spiritual progression.  Even
though this time may cause some consternation or make you feel unsettled
temporarily, you will soon have a sense of relief and freedom.  Rise up
and rejoice in a new beginning, says the Lord.
Psalm 146:5-10 Happy is he who has the God of Jacob for his help, whose
hope is in the LORD his God, Who made heaven and earth, the sea, and all
that is in them; Who keeps truth forever, Who executes justice for the
oppressed, Who gives food to the hungry. The LORD gives freedom to the
prisoners.  The LORD opens the eyes of the blind; the LORD raises those
who are bowed down; the LORD loves the righteous.   The LORD watches
over the strangers; He relieves the fatherless and widow; but the way of
the wicked He turns upside down.  The LORD shall reign forever----Your
God, O Zion, to all generations. Praise the LORD!

Beloved, quiet your soul and discern.  Satan has sent a prince of
darkness against you to block the anointing and stop the flow of My
Spirit in your midst.  Its operation is like the  jamming of radio
signals, and it covers you with a spiritual blanket of fog to hinder My
work in and around you.  Its purpose is to bring discouragement and
condemnation to you.  Rise up, My people and break this assignment, shut
the door in the devil's face, and allow your faith to become a shield
against this intrusion.  I declare to you that victory is assured, says
the Lord.
Ephesians 6:12 For we do not wrestle against flesh and blood, but
against principalities, against powers, against the rulers of the
darkness of this age, against spiritual hosts of wickedness in the
heavenly places.

I will do a particular and valuable work in your heart if you will allow
it.  I will reveal all stubbornness and rebellion that cause you to want
things to be according to own your will instead of yielding by the
Spirit to My will.  Your unwillingness springs from your carnal nature
and hinders the flow of spiritual blessings in your life.  I speak to
many who have lived your life trying to manipulate situations,
circumstances and people so that you could be in control.  The sense of
being in control is a comfort to your flesh, but it hinders the flow of
My Spirit.  My ways are higher than your ways, and My thoughts than your
thoughts.  I will bring you to your highest good and greatest blessings
if you will allow Me to do this work, says the Lord.
Galatians 6:8 For he who sows to his flesh will of the flesh reap
corruption, but he who sows to the Spirit will of the Spirit reap
everlasting life.

You can expect for the spiritual fog to begin to lift so that you can
see with greater clarity.  The decisions that you make at this time will
be born out of truth and justice rather than coming from a need to
simply survive.  You can enter into this place of righteous momentum by
the Spirit, which will open a direct way through a maze of dead ends
that you have experienced in the recent past.  But, you must align your
will with Mine, says the Lord, by asking in faith for divine guidance
and then by yielding to My direction.
Proverbs 4:12 When you walk, your steps will not be hindered, And when
you run, you will not stumble.

My people, you will now begin to see the unveiling of a new order in My
kingdom.  In this time I will establish truth and justice, and in  this
process hidden indiscretions will come to light and will be judged, for
you are entering a time of disclosure.  By the same token, those who
have committed sins and have lost fellowship with Me will begin to seek
to be restored to their kingdom position.  Their restoration will depend
on whether or not they are truly repentant.  Those who have an ear to
hear will begin to raise up a standard of spiritual and moral integrity
for this new plateau.  You will be required to question what you really
believe, and thus define your doctrine more precisely.  You will have to
examine your code of ethics to make sure that your responses are
consistent with the Word.   Be on guard, for this new level of kingdom
experience will be met with opposition from the enemy.  This war will be
called the Battle of Integrity as you face circumstances, situations,
tests and trials that reveal your heart.  War is always required to take
new spiritual territory.  If you yield to the work of My Spirit, you can
win these battles one decision at a time as you establish and maintain
integrity.  You, My Church, are in a process of preparation, which will
result in your being without spot and blameless, says the Lord.
Ephesians 5:25 -27  Husbands, love your wives, just as Christ also loved
the church and gave Himself for her, that He might sanctify and cleanse
her with the washing of water by the word, that He might present her to
Himself a glorious church, not having spot or wrinkle or any such thing,
but that she should be holy and without blemish.

